# grok-cli Tools System

## Core Components
- Registry & Dispatch (`tools/registry.rs`)
- Tool Definitions & Schemas
- Execution Context (`ToolContext`)

## Tool Categories
- **File Tools** — read, write, replace, search, glob, list
- **Shell Tools** — run_shell_command with timeout & policy
- **Web Tools** — web_search, web_fetch
- **MCP Bridge** — mcp_call, mcp_list, dynamic server tools
- **Agent Coordination** — spawn_agent, send_message, team_*, fork/join
- **Memory & Archive** — save_memory, recall_context
- **Task Management** — task_create, task_update, task_get, execute_task_graph
- **Planning & Worktrees** — enter/exit_plan_mode, enter/exit_worktree
- **Skills & Discovery** — execute_skill, list_skills, tool_search, cron_create
- **LSP Integration** — lsp_query (diagnostics, hover, definitions)
- **System Utilities** — sleep, synthetic_output, generate_commit_message

## Security & Control
- ToolPolicy (read/write/execute permissions)
- Sandbox (`tools/sandbox.rs`)
- Tool Arbitration (`tool_arbitration.rs`)
- Permission Bridge (ACP)

## MCP Integration (Phase 1–4)
- Servers connected on `session/new`
- Tools discovered via `tools/list`
- Exposed as `server:tool_name` (e.g. `markmap:generate`)
- `mcp_list` tool for inspection
- Global registry for cross-session visibility

## Key Files
- `src/tools/registry.rs`
- `src/tools/mod.rs`
- `src/acp/mcp_bridge.rs`
- `src/mcp/client.rs`

## Notes
- All tools are OpenAI function-calling compatible
- Full JSON schemas returned by `get_full_tool_definitions()`
- MCP tools are merged at runtime when servers are connected